devdoc.details: This contract handles the logic for minting, burning, and managing NFTs in the Pixotchi game.

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

Initialized(uint8).details: Triggered when the contract has been initialized or reinitialized.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

_getPlantsByOwner(address).details: Returns detailed information about plants owned by a specific address.

returns._0: An array of detailed information about the plants owned by the address.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to be burned.

getPlantInfo(uint256).details: Returns detailed information about a plant.

returns._0: The detailed information about the plant.

getPlantInfoExtended(uint256).details: Returns detailed information about a plant, including extensions.

returns._0: The detailed information about the plant, including extensions.

getPlantScore(uint256).details: Returns the score of a plant.

getPlantStatusRange(uint256,uint256).details: Returns information about plants that are alive or dead, but not burned, within a specified ID range.

params.fromId: The starting ID of the range (inclusive).
params.toId: The ending ID of the range (inclusive).

returns._0: An array of PlantStatus structs containing information about the plants.

getPlantTimeUntilStarving(uint256).details: Returns the time until a plant starts starving.

returns._0: The time until the plant starts starving.

getPlantsByOwner(address).details: Returns detailed information about plants owned by a specific address.

returns._0: An array of detailed information about the plants owned by the address.

getPlantsByOwnerExtended(address).details: Returns detailed information about plants owned by a specific address, including extensions.

returns._0: An array of detailed information about the plants owned by the address, including extensions.

getPlantsInfo(uint256[]).details: Returns detailed information about multiple plants.

returns._0: An array of detailed information about the plants.

getPlantsInfoExtended(uint256[]).details: Returns detailed information about multiple plants, including extensions.

returns._0: An array of detailed information about the plants, including extensions.

initializeNFTLogic().details: Initializes the NFTLogic contract. Sets up the initial state of the contract, including the token, admin, and revenue share wallet addresses.

mint(uint256).details: Mints a new NFT with the specified strain.

params.strain: The strain of the NFT to be minted.

removeTokenIdFromOwner(uint32,address).details: Removes a token ID from the owner's list of tokens.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to be removed.

tokenBurnAndRedistribute(address,uint256.details: Burns tokens and redistributes them according to the burn percentage.

params.account: The account from which tokens will be burned.
params.amount: The amount of tokens to be burned.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the token URI for a given token ID.

totalSupply().details: Burned tokens are calculated here, use _totalMinted() if you want to count just minted tokens.

devdoc.title: NFTLogic

ApprovalCallerNotOwnerNorApproved().notice: The caller must own the token or be an approved operator.

ApprovalToCurrentOwner().notice: The caller cannot approve to the current owner.

ApproveToCaller().notice: The caller cannot approve to their own address.

BalanceQueryForZeroAddress().notice: Cannot query the balance for the zero address.

MintToZeroAddress().notice: Cannot mint to the zero address.

MintZeroQuantity().notice: The quantity of tokens minted must be more than zero.

TransferCallerNotOwnerNorApproved().notice: The caller must own the token or be an approved operator.

TransferFromIncorrectOwner().notice: The token must be owned by `from`.

TransferToNonERC721ReceiverImplementer().notice: Cannot safely transfer to a contract that does not implement the ERC721Receiver interface.

TransferToZeroAddress().notice: Cannot transfer to the zero address.
